<br />Talking about the top-loader: :-)  It might seem like I'm being OCD ("who touches their carts once they're inserted?!") but honestly I'm not.  The problem is that many carts simply don't work until you wiggle them around or find the "perfect angle" for them to be at.  Someone bumps my table, puts down a cup of tea, whatever -- game crashes.  Serious bummer.
<br />
<br />Switching back to the front-loader: connector pitch (being discussed here) almost sounds like what this problem is, re: chykn stating that the cartridge connector has to be perfectly centred/aligned (vertically and horizontally).  I wonder if the connector I bought has the wrong pitch.  Hmm.

		

